JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 66
IS  - 1
SP  - 115
EP  - 138
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - In the last few years, a new area has emerged in economic theory, which goes under the heading of “incomplete contracting” However, almost since its inception, the theory has been under attack for its lack of rigorous foundations. In this paper, we evaluate some of the criticisms that have been made of the theory, in particular, those in Maskin and Tirole (1999a). In doing so, we develop a model that provides a rigorous foundation for the idea that contracts are incomplete.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1111/1467-937X.00080
ER  - 



